# Concept Pages

Every concept page has exactly 7 sections with these ids:

1. `hook` — analogy, no jargon
2. `why-it-matters` — failure narrative (what breaks without this)
3. `interactive-viz` — animation-first teaching
4. `core-mechanism` — technical details
5. `tradeoffs` — use-when / poor-fit-when
6. `connections` — prerequisites and downstream concepts
7. `check-understanding` — quiz (the gate)

## Adding a concept

1. Copy `site/_template/concept-leaf.html` → `site/topics/<topic>/<concept-slug>.html`
2. Create `site/js/topics/<topic>/<concept-slug>-data.js` (quiz, viz config)
3. Update `site/topics/<topic>/index.html` (link card)
4. Update `site/js/topics/registry.js` (reading order)

## Slug alignment (critical)

These three must match exactly (kebab-case):

- Topic `id` in `registry.js`
- `data-progress-ring` on the progress ring container
- `initProgress('<topic-id>', '<concept-slug>')` call
- `data-quiz-id` on `.quiz-container` must match concept slug

## Viz and quiz attributes

- `data-viz-type` must exist in `pipeline-viz.js` mountAll() switch
- Quiz needs ≥ 2 MC questions with `correct` index and `explanation`
- Include `<noscript>` fallback for the interactive viz
